{"comments":"Verify — Satisfiability checking for layout constraints.\n\nUses Fourier-Motzkin elimination for linear arithmetic over rationals.\nFor integer constraints, this provides a sound (but incomplete) check:\nif FM says UNSAT over rationals, then definitely UNSAT over integers.\n\n## Why Fourier-Motzkin?\n\nAt billion-agent scale, we need agents to quickly determine:\n\"Can this layout even fit?\" before wasting compute on optimization.\n\nFM elimination is:\n- Complete for linear arithmetic over reals/rationals\n- Sound for integers (UNSAT propagates, SAT may be spurious)\n- Pure and deterministic (no FFI, no randomness)\n- Polynomial in practice for layout constraints\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nFormula → normalize → eliminateAll → checkFeasibility → VerifyResult\n```\n\nStatus: FOUNDATIONAL\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Layout","Verify"],"Witness"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[169,8],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Layout/Verify.purs","start":[169,3]},"title":"Sat"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[170,10],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Layout/Verify.purs","start":[170,3]},"title":"Unsat"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[171,12],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Layout/Verify.purs","start":[171,3]},"title":"Unknown"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Layout","Verify"],"VerifyResult"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[173,50],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Layout/Verify.purs","start":[173,1]},"title":"eqVerifyResult"}],"comments":"Verification result for constraint satisfiability.\n\n## Witness Construction\n\nWhen SAT, the witness may be empty. This is sound: it means we proved\nfeasibility exists, but didn't construct specific values. For layout\nverification, knowing feasibility is sufficient — the actual values\ncome from the ILP solver.\n\nFor a trivial witness, all variables can be set to 0 if the constraints\nallow (i.e., 0 satisfies all bounds). The Fourier-Motzkin elimination\nproves this is possible when all residual bounds are non-negative.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[171,12],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Layout/Verify.purs","start":[168,1]},"title":"VerifyResult"},{"children":[],"comments":"Witness: variable assignments that satisfy the constraints.\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Tuple"],"Tuple"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Layout","Constraint"],"Var"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},"tag":"ParensInType"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[133,40],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Layout/Verify.purs","start":[133,1]},"title":"Witness"},{"children":[],"comments":"Verify satisfiability of normalized constraints.\n\nUses Fourier-Motzkin elimination followed by back-substitution\nto construct a witness when the constraints are satisfiable.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Layout","Verify"],"NormalConstraint"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Layout","Verify"],"VerifyResult"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[639,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Layout/Verify.purs","start":[639,1]},"title":"verifySat"},{"children":[],"comments":"Verify satisfiability of a formula.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Layout","Constraint"],"Formula"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Layout","Verify"],"VerifyResult"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[630,41],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Layout/Verify.purs","start":[630,1]},"title":"verifyFormula"},{"children":[],"comments":"Normalized constraint: Σ aᵢxᵢ ≤ b\n\nAll constraints are converted to this form:\n- `t ≤ 0` becomes coefficients with constant on right\n- `t ≥ 0` becomes `-t ≤ 0`\n- `t = 0` becomes two constraints: `t ≤ 0` and `-t ≤ 0`\n- `t < 0` becomes `t + ε ≤ 0` (approximated as `t ≤ -1` for integers)\n- `t > 0` becomes `-t < 0`\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["coeffs",{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Tuple"],"Tuple"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Layout","Constraint"],"Var"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},"tag":"ParensInType